-- DuplicateSignature (S-2, 2026-07-13): a top-level name carries its OWN
-- second type signature — same arity, contiguous with the first, no
-- intervening declaration.  This used to be silently coalesced into "one
-- multi-clause function" with zero diagnostics (the gap dupValueBindingErrors
-- and contiguityErrors both missed: neither fires on a CONTIGUOUS same-arity
-- run).  A legitimate multi-clause function has exactly one signature; two
-- signatures for the same name is unambiguously two definitions.
--
-- NOTE on the golden text below: this fixture's oracle (resolve_main /
-- diagnostics_main, both driven by the PLAIN `parse` entry — see
-- frontend/parser.mdk's `parse` vs `parseLocated`) never threads real source
-- positions, so the embedded "already defined at line 1" always reads line 1
-- regardless of this file's true line 8 — a pre-existing, documented property
-- of these specific harnesses ("locations are dropped... matching
-- dev/diagdump.exe --resolve", top of this file), not a bug in the check
-- itself. The real CLI (`medaka check`, which parses via `parseLocated`)
-- reports the true line — verified: `medaka check` on this exact file says
-- "already defined at line 8", and `medaka check --json`'s `range` correctly
-- points at line 11 (the second signature).
foo : Int -> Int
foo x = x + 1

foo : Int -> Int
foo x = x * 2
